The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, specifically the density of subgraphs of Cartesian products of graphs. This falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses VC-dimension and VC-density, which are concepts from computational geometry (cs.CG) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper mentions adjacency labeling schemes, which are used in distributed computing and communication complexity (cs.CC).
